import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

y = ['Loan']
X = .drop(columns=['Loan'])
X = pd.get_dummies(X, columns=['Checking Account', 'Savings Account', 'Property'])
X['Credit Amount'] = np.log(X['Credit Amount'])
#  - normalize      ,     , normalize  
# X[['Duration', 'Credit Amount', 'Age']] = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X[['Duration', 'Credit Amount', 'Age']])
print(X.head())

X_, X_, y_, y_ = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.25, random_state=0)

#  ML  
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.discriminant_analysis import LinearDiscriminantAnalysis
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from xgboost import XGBClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold, cross_val_score
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report

_ = []
_.append(('LR', LogisticRegression(C=10)))
_.append(('LDA', LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()))
_.append(('KNN', KNeighborsClassifier()))
_.append(('CART', DecisionTreeClassifier()))
_.append(('NB', GaussianNB()))
_.append(('RF', RandomForestClassifier()))
_.append(('SVM', SVC(gamma='auto')))
_.append(('XGB', XGBClassifier(verbosity=0)))

__ = []
__ = []
_ = []
 = 'accuracy'

for ,  in _:
    k_ = KFold(n_splits=10)
    _ = cross_val_score(, X, y, cv=k_, scoring=)
    __.append(_)
    _.append()
    print(f"{}: {} Avg: {_.mean():.2} Std {_.std():.2}")
    .fit(X_, y_)
     = .predict(X_)
    print(f"Test Dataset : {classification_report(y_, )}")
    _ = classification_report(y_, , output_dict=True)
    __.append({'model': ,'type' : 'accuracy', 'value' : _['accuracy']})
    __.append({'model': ,'type' : 'precision', 'value' : _['1']['precision']})
    __.append({'model': ,'type' : 'recall', 'value' : _['1']['recall']})
    __.append({'model': ,'type' : 'f1-score', 'value' : _['1']['f1-score']})

# PDD, ICE plot
#  : https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/partial_dependence.html
#  - sklearn 0.24  

from sklearn.inspection import partial_dependence
from sklearn.inspection import plot_partial_dependence

# 
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,15))
axs = fig.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=2)
plot_partial_dependence(, X_, ['Sex', 'Age', 'Duration', 'Credit Amount'], kind='both', 
                        subsample=50,
                        grid_resolution=50, ax=axs)
for ax in axs.flat:
    ax.legend_ = None
    ax.grid(True, axis='y', color='gray', alpha=0.5, linestyle='--')
plt.show()
